        <name>sampleProportion</name>
        <param>
          <type>double</type>
          <declname>proportion</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Determine the number of samples to draw as a proportion of the total number. That is, we draw <computeroutput>count = totalCount * proportion</computeroutput> samples. This option is overridden when an absolute count is specified by <ref refid="classvigra_1_1SamplerOptions_1a851a757874c19a2e2ac7d918216c973e" kindref="member">sampleSize()</ref>. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>If stratifiedSampling is true, the count is equally distributed across all strata (e.g. <computeroutput>totalCount * proportion / strataCount</computeroutput> samples are taken from each stratum).</para><para><linebreak/>
 Default: 1.0 </para>        </detaileddescription>
