        <definition>SamplerOptions&amp; stratified</definition>
        <argsstring>(bool in=true)</argsstring>
        <name>stratified</name>
        <param>
          <type>bool</type>
          <declname>in</declname>
          <defval>true</defval>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Draw equally many samples from each &quot;stratum&quot;. A stratum is a group of like entities, e.g. pixels belonging to the same object class. This is useful to create balanced samples when the class probabilities are very unbalanced (e.g. when there are many background and few foreground pixels). Stratified sampling thus avoids that a trained classifier is biased towards the majority class. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><linebreak/>
 Default (if you don&apos;t call this function): false </para>        </detaileddescription>
